        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(state): graceful chmodSync on filesystems without POSIX support",
        "body": "## Problem\n\n`ensureOpenClawStatePermissions` calls `chmodSync` on the state directory and sidecar files, which crashes the gateway on filesystems that do not support POSIX permissions.\n\n**Affected filesystems:**\n- Docker volume drivers\n- Azure Files (SMB/NFS)\n- NFS mounts without `no_root_squash`\n- Certain Kubernetes PVC storage classes\n\n**Impact:** P1 regression — gateway crashes at startup before serving any requests.\n\nFixes #91919\n\n## Root Cause\n\n`ensureOpenClawStatePermissions` is called in two places inside `openOpenClawStateDatabase` without error handling:\n- Line ~843: before opening the SQLite handle\n- Line ~860: after schema setup\n\nBoth `chmodSync(dir, ...)` and `chmodSync(candidate, ...)` throw on unsupported filesystems.\n\n## Fix\n\nWrap both `chmodSync` calls in try-catch with graceful fallback. The gateway can still start and operate normally — the only lost behavior is the file permission enforcement, which is irrelevant on filesystems that do not support POSIX permissions anyway.\n\n## Files Changed\n\n1. `src/state/openclaw-state-db.ts` — Wrap `chmodSync` calls in try-catch\n2. `src/state/openclaw-state-db.test.ts` — Add test mocking `chmodSync` to throw\n\n## Testing\n\n- [x] TypeScript transpiles without errors\n- [x] New test: `opens the database even when chmodSync throws on unsupported filesystems`\n  - Mocks `fs.chmodSync` to always throw EPERM\n  - Verifies database opens successfully despite chmod failures\n\n## Checklist\n\n- [x] I have read the Contributor Guide\n- [x] I have signed the CNCF CLA\n- [x] I have added tests that prove my fix is effective\n- [x] I have rebased my branch on top of the latest main",
